ğŸ“ Shift From Outputs to Outcomes Instead of tracking effort-based metrics (e.g., velocity or hours worked), focus on metrics that highlight delivered value:
- Customer Satisfaction: Are we solving real problems?
- Cycle Time: How quickly can we turn ideas into usable features?
- Business Impact: How is our work driving ROI or achieving strategic goals?
ğŸ“ Incorporate Team Health Metrics Sustainable delivery requires healthy teams. Metrics like team morale, engagement, and psychological safety can indicate long-term success.
ğŸ“ Make Metrics Actionable A good metric inspires change. Ask yourself:
- What decision will this data help us make?
- Does it align with our Agile values?

